This paper is about optimization methods for solving convex optimization problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of coordinate descent methods and support vector machines suggest that the paper is likely to be in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The numerical evidence with Lasso suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The use of adaptive rules based on dual residual or primal-dual gap estimates suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the use of hinge-loss support vector machines suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
